{"ID":270325, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"325\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs324.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs326.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 325<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The disappointment of hopes and expectations at the resurrection would be indescribably\n  dreadful.<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Angels and Spirits<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">The organization of the spiritual and heavenly worlds,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and of spiritual and heavenly beings,\n  was agreeable to the most perfect order and harmony:<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> their limits and bounds were fixed<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span>\n  irrevocably, and voluntarily subscribed to in their heavenly estate by themselves, and were by our\n  first parents<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> subscribed to upon the earth. Hence the importance of embracing and subscribing to\n  principles of eternal truth by all men upon the earth that expect eternal life.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I assure the Saints that truth, in reference to these matters, can and may be known through the\n  revelations of God in the way of His ordinances,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> and in answer to prayer.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> The Hebrew Church\n  &ldquo;came unto the spirits of just men made perfect,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> and unto an innumerable company of angels,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> unto\n  God the Father of all,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> and to Jesus Christ the Mediator of the new covenant.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> What did they learn\n  by coming to the spirits of just men made perfect?<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> Is it written? No. What they learned has not\n  been and could not have been written.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> What object was gained by this communication with the\n  spirits of the just?<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> It was the established order of the kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> of God: The keys of power and\n  knowledge<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> were with them to communicate to the Saints. Hence the importance of understanding\n  the distinction between the spirits of the just and angels.<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Spirits can only be revealed in flaming fire and glory.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> Angels have advanced further, their\n  light and glory being tabernacled;<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and hence they appear in bodily shape.<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> The spirits of just men<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span>\n  are made ministering servants to those who<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> are sealed unto life eternal,<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> and it is through them that\n  the sealing power comes down.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Patriarch Adams is now one of the spirits of the just men made perfect;<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> and, if revealed now,\n  must be revealed in fire;<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> and the glory could not be endured.<span class=\"footRef\">27<\/span> Jesus showed Himself to His\n  disciples, and they thought it was His spirit, and they were afraid to approach His spirit.<span class=\"footRef\">28<\/span> Angels\n  have advanced higher in knowledge and power than spirits.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Concerning Brother James Adams, it should appear strange that so good and so great a man was\n  hated. The deceased ought never to have had an enemy. But so it was. Wherever<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110249\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110249)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110249)\">Heb. 10:26-27<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111424\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111424)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111424)\">Jacob 6:13<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111546\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111546)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111546)\">Mosiah 3:25<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112279\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112279)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112279)\">Alma 40:14<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115317\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115317)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115317)\">D&amp;C 104:18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117060\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117060)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117060)\">Abr. 4:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"117014\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 117014)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(117014)\">Abr. 3:1-10<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114841\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 114841)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(114841)\">D&amp;C 88:42-43<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115780\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115780)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115780)\">D&amp;C 121:30-31<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110934\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110934)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110934)\">1 Ne. 5:11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112305\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112305)\">&nbsp;<\/a